Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay near fine buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 31, 18? Name Menodoros. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0696.57.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1185)
